South African rapper Riky Rick has died. AFP/Miguel Medina JOHANNESBURG - South African rapper Riky Rick has died. The musician, entrepreneur and fashion designer was 34 years old. He is best known for Sondela, Stay Shining and Boss Zonke. Rikhado Muziwendlovu Makhado will be remembered as a visionary artist. His record label Cotton Club Records has helped numerous artists break out. He also launched Cotton Fest, a festival that merges music and fashion and gives young artists a platform. The circumstances around his death have not been confirmed.